sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1055007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The part enables the user to produce functional cutinase from fungus Fusarium solani pisi which is a cuticula degrading hydrolase. The enzyme is fused to mRFP to allow tracking of expression and also provides a His-Tag for subsequent purification. Both, mRFP and His-Tag, can be cleaved using TEV-Protease.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sven Jager, Sebastian Wagner and Anne Schieferdecker
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Despite BioBricks the part also consists of the RBS from pET22b(+), a TEV-site and a His-Tag.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PelB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PelB leader sequence; directs protein to E. coli periplasmic membrane
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The pelB leader sequence is a sequence of amino acids which when attached to a protein, directs the protein to the periplasmic membrane of E. coli, where the sequence is removed by pelB peptidase. It is used to direct coat protein-antigen fusions to the cell surface.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Austen Heinz

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K808025
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A cutinase is a cuticula degrading hydrolase from the fungus Fusarium solani pisi. It shows activity towards PET.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Marie Burghard, Henrik Cordes, Jascha Diemer, Adrian Eilingsfeld, Sven Jager, Rene Sahm, Arne Wehling
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Cloned from vector pEST100 from Becker et all 2005: (Becker, S., Theile, S., Heppeler, N., Michalczyk, A., Wentzel, A., Wilhelm, S., Jaeger, K.-E., et al. (2005). A generic system for the Escherichia coli cell-surface display of lipolytic enzymes. FEBS letters, 579(5), 1177???82. doi:10.1016/j.febslet.2004.12.087)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Surface Expression is very hard to do. FsC shows lipolytic activity and attacks the outer membrane of gramm negativ bacteria. This activity leads to a certain toxicity for expression hosts. In addition FsC needs to be expressed in the periplasm due to folding issues.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
